  "body": "When I run the simplest form of `run-container`:\n\n```\n$ kubectl run-container vmarmol-secret vmarmol/secret:latest\n```\n\nI expected this to be a one-time pod (it is a command I was running to test HTTPS connections and exits quickly). However, in reality it created a replicaController pod. According to the examples in kubectl.sh:\n\n```\n    $ kubectl run-container nginx --image=dockerfile/nginx\n    // Starts a single instance of nginx.\n\n    $ kubectl run-container nginx --image=dockerfile/nginx --replicas=5\n    // Starts a replicated instance of nginx.\n```\n\nI was expecting to need to use the `--replicas` flag in order to get that behavior. Is this intended? The implementation currently takes the default of `--replicas=1` which probably explains the behavior.\n",
